{"component":"McpHandlers","context":{"args":{"content":"The project will be called **Numa Radio**.\n\nThe main public domain will be **numaradio.com**.\n\nThe public website/frontend will be hosted on **Vercel**.\n\nThe **NanoClaw** backend runs **locally on a dedicated always-on mini-server** at home (used purely for the website — not the user's day-to-day laptop).\n\nBecause a live public website cannot directly access a local network service, the local NanoClaw service is exposed through **Cloudflare Tunnel**. Cloudflare Tunnel was chosen over alternatives (ngrok, localtunnel, etc.) for being the most reliable option with a usable free tier.\n\nThe planned structure is:\n\n- `numaradio.com` → public website/frontend on Vercel\n    \n- `api.numaradio.com` → Cloudflare Tunnel → local NanoClaw service running on the dedicated mini-server\n    \n\nThis setup is suitable for MVP. The mini-server is intended to remain powered on and running NanoClaw continuously. Migration to managed cloud hosting (e.g. Fly, Railway, Hetzner, AWS) is a planned later step once the product is stable.\n\nUpdated 2026-04-19: confirmed dedicated mini-server (not laptop), always-on, Cloudflare Tunnel locked.\n\nDesign is here: [[Numa Radio Design]]","filepath":"SaaS/Numa Radio/4. Branding and Hosting Update.md"},"toolName":"obsidian_update_content"},"level":"info","message":"Executing tool: obsidian_update_content","timestamp":"2026-04-19T09:40:43.403Z"}
