{"component":"McpHandlers","context":{"args":{"content":"# Numa Radio — Decisions Log\n\nLiving record of decisions made in chat that aren't already captured elsewhere in the vault. Newest at top.\n\n---\n\n## 2026-04-19\n\n### Catalog size\n- Launch with **~50 songs**, not 500. Catalog grows over time.\n- Single-artist seed: **Russell Ross**. The site copy and queue rotation rules should not over-emphasize artist names since one identity covers most plays at launch.\n\n### Hosting\n- Frontend: `numaradio.com` on **Vercel**.\n- Backend: `api.numaradio.com` → **Cloudflare Tunnel** → dedicated **always-on home mini-server** (NOT the user's day-to-day laptop).\n- Cloudflare Tunnel chosen for reliability + free tier.\n- MVP-acceptable. Migration to managed cloud (Fly / Railway / Hetzner / AWS) is a planned later step.\n\n### Database\n- **Neon Postgres** (eu-west-2, pooled). Verified reachable on 2026-04-19 (PostgreSQL 17.8).\n- Connection string lives in `.env.local` as `DATABASE_URL`.\n\n### Music generation\n- **MiniMax 2.6** via `https://api.minimax.io/v1/music_generation`.\n- Existing code worth reusing from sibling project `make-noise/app/api/music/route.ts`:\n  - Response normalization (duration units vary — ns/μs/ms/samples; the route normalizes to ms).\n  - Async polling pattern (180 attempts × 2s = ~6 min).\n  - Mood + genre prompt prefix concatenation.\n- Env var: **`MINIMAX_API_KEY`** (matches blueprint).\n- Status endpoint `/api/music/status?task_id=...` is referenced in the make-noise client but the route file isn't in the tree — needs to be confirmed or rebuilt when porting.\n\n### Host voice (Lena)\n- **Deepgram Aura** for MVP. Migrate to **ElevenLabs** later for more emotional range.\n- Recommended starting voice: **`aura-2-luna-en`** (warm, late-night DJ feel) over Asteria (used in `read-for-me`, more clear/energetic).\n- Existing code worth reusing from sibling project `read-for-me`:\n  - `app/api/synthesize/route.ts` — full Aura TTS with chunking (600 soft / 1600 hard cap), primary→fallback model, PCM concat, WAV wrap. **Highly reusable**, just swap model env + change return path (upload to B2 instead of streaming back).\n  - `lib/radio-host.ts` — text→radio cadence: 8–14 word phrases, clause-boundary splits, \"Up next.\" cadence cues, quote marks around \"Numa Radio\". **Directly reusable for Lena's segments.**\n  - `lib/strip-markdown.ts` — input sanitization, useful before TTS.\n- Note: `read-for-me` uses env var `DEEPGRAM_API`. Blueprint specifies `DEEPGRAM_API_KEY`. Standardize on **`DEEPGRAM_API_KEY`**.\n\n### Suno-link request flow (NEW request type beyond blueprint)\n- The design surfaces three submission types: Song / Shoutout / **Suno link**.\n- Legal concern: a listener pasting `suno.com/song/...` may not be the song's commercial-rights holder — Suno grants commercial use to the *paid creator*, not anyone who has the URL.\n- **Decision (MVP):** auto-fetch metadata only (title, prompt summary, duration). Store as `request_type=suno_link`, status `pending_review`. **No auto-airing.** User (operator) approves which Suno-link submissions enter rotation, manually.\n- Public copy on success screen: *\"Sent to Lena's inbox — she picks favourites for a listener Suno rotation.\"*\n- Track provenance keeps `source_type=suno_listener_link` distinct so any track can be pulled fast if rights questions appear.\n\n### Stream delivery protocol\n- **Open question.** Three real options:\n  1. **Icecast + Liquidsoap** (battle-tested, full radio-station stack, slightly heavyweight).\n  2. **HLS** (CDN-friendly, ~10–20s latency, easier on infra).\n  3. **Server-time-synced HTML5 audio** (cheapest, fragile).\n- Not yet decided. Picking this gates Phase 1.\n\n---\n\n## Memory notes\n\nThis project also has an internal Claude memory at `~/.claude/projects/-Users-sisin-Developer-numaradio/memory/` (not visible in the vault). Vault is the source of truth for product decisions; memory is for collaboration patterns and live conversational state.\n","filepath":"SaaS/Numa Radio/Decisions Log.md"},"toolName":"obsidian_update_content"},"level":"info","message":"Executing tool: obsidian_update_content","timestamp":"2026-04-19T09:55:45.770Z"}
